				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Glad the pacing worked for you, that paragraph also felt essential to me, which was why it was so difficult to cut this down. &#8220;Created brute couplings to assist the combustions of motion&#8221; is the one phrase I really had to fight, and it&#8217;s about a third the length it should be, so I have to agree it doesn&#8217;t quite work. It will in the longer version. She says, in tones of low menace.</p>
<p>Interestingly, I didn&#8217;t see the grandfather as a mechanic, my mental image was my own grandfather, retired and fiddling with cars for fun &#8211; hence yard and grass et al. </p>
<p>but I&#8217;m happy you enjoyed this.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

